rComments: For global fiction, she assigned a large amount of reading that she could neither provide interesting lectures around nor successfully examine in depth with the short time provided during the quarter. Her voice is high pitched and very irking and she seems to think she is the goddess of theory, which she certainly isn't. Should take tips from Jody.

Cooppan is a brilliant, inspiring Lit professor and probably one of the kindest. Altho very complex material, she brought together diverse forms of analysis in an exciting way. She led a great discussion group thru challenging conceptual terrain, yet never once put anyone on the spot-just consistently showed respect & encouragement. Do the reading!

Professor Cooppan is so nice and very accommodating. She is extremely intelligent. I had to give a presentation in class and I was nervous and she did everything in her power to make me feel comfortable. I'd take a class with her again but I'm graduating. I'd recommend her to anyone-she is an incredible professor.

Prof. Cooppan is extremely intelligent and I was initially intimidated to speak during class but she is really helpful. When materials were dense, she would allow extra time to to help us dissect the readings and she is extremely encouraging and wants her students to gain a good experience of her class. interesting materials, not jargon..

Pretty much the worst professor ever. The class was Global Fiction, but over half our novels were about Africa. Little focus on Europe and NO focus on Asia or South America. Lectures were pointless but mandatory. Her "insight" is filled with jargon and will eventually go to points that no longer relate to the novel. Never take a class from her.
She is a GREAT professor. My absolute favorite in the literature department. She professors much of her own theory, and was recently published. Definitely worth taking a class!

Prof Coopann is SO COOL (& sexy). The readings were always relevant to lecture, so nothing felt like a waste of time. Although there was some dense theory to get through, she always took her time to unpack it and make sure the class understood the big ideas. Definitely wants the students to do well and have fun. I highly recommend her!!

Professor Cooppan has a nice personality but is not a good teacher.  Her lectures were the most difficult to follow of any class I have taken, because she uses a large amount of jargon and takes a long time to get to any given point.  However, I enjoyed the novels assigned for The Postcolonial Novel in India and Africa.

Very engaging and helpful. She always gave back great written and oral comments on all work. It was a lot of reading, but definitely manageable. She is very approachable and I was able to build a lasting relationship with her outside of class that has helped me greatly in other areas.

I think my major problem with this class wasn't solely Dr. Cooppan's fault - there were a few students who thought that their "insights" were worthy of a lot of class time, and they weren't. But she indulged them. She's a nice woman, but not the greatest at teaching. Or lecturing. Interesting material; boring, pretentious and mandatory lectures.

A dissapointing class. Her lectures were uninspired and boring, but attendance is still mandatory. Also, the other people in the class talked WAY too much, and she encouraged every stupid comment. We read good books, but it was a waste of time, unfortunately.

Global Narratives: lots of reading but interesting texts. Two papers, one midterm, one final. DO THE READING, and you'll be fine. Also, if you want a grade higher than a B on the tests, study the handouts - they are emailed to you daily. She's a very good speaker/lecturer, and really listens to what you have to say.

Lackluster at best, seems to dwell on obvious points and coddles the people that love to share their mundane opinion for half the lecture. Picks a great selection of readings though her supplementaries are arbitrary at best, TESTS MORE ON HANDOUTS THAN READINGS. Your TA is your grade, make sure you have a good one or switch. Disappointing overall.

I've taken 2 classes with her. Heavy reading load, but she picks cool texts, and she's very intelligent, responsive, and an eloquent speaker. Her voice is easy to listen to, and she always takes what students say seriously. She never makes people feel stupid, which is refreshing.

Vilashni is an awesome professor. She chose excellent texts and delivers spectacular lectures. Very helpful prof. who brings a new element to a lot of old works (Like Heart of Darkness) Highly recommended. Don't listen to the whining 1st years. They're just cranky at 8 AM.

Mandatory class would not be a problem if this prof were decent. She isn't: She's just pretentious, uses fancy words to hide fact that she has absolutely nothing to say. Empty, soulless, seems driven by professional ambition rather than by curiosity or any desire to be a decent teacher. Makes even graphic novels boring. Avoid, avoid, avoid.

had her for her first quarter teaching at ucsc, thought she was excellent. ALL Lit 1 classes are at 8am, so stop complaining. Good use of texts, but a lot of reading. Keep up with the reading, which is my advice for EVERY lit class.

This was an incredibly easy class. I did not like the mandatory lectures and the TAs were terrible, but I thought Vilashini did a good job. I was worried about reading a graphic novel, but it completely blew my mind. More professors need to be more daring about their choices in books like she is.

It would be the easiest class ever except for the fact that mandatory lecture was at 8 AM and in the middle of nowhere. She has interesting taste in literature but is hell of pretentious. Good for getting the W requirement out of the way I guess, but it requires a lot of free time for an entry level class.
Yea shes very fine looking but it sux that the classes have to be mandatory and at 8am, other than that not too bad a class save her weirdo ta's
I really enjoyed this class. She was a great teacher, but it does suck that its at 8am
her lectures were pretty boring but the readings were very interesting along with the writing assingments...she's just a nice, enthusiastic person which is nice
OMG, she is UBERboring. It's hard to tell if she's hard or not because the TAs grade everything. But yeah, mandatory attendance sucks.

Professor Cooppan definetely has a bit of a supremecy thing going on, but her brilliance more than compensates for a little ego.  The selected readings all work well together.  I think she has trouble remembering that Lit1 is not upper-d and she has to connect the texts for the people that are in it for the gen eds.  And she is unbelievably hot.

She's such a bad lecturer. Her notes are scattered and she requires MANDATORY attendence when they're futile. She's nice... but SO BORING and SOOOO pretentious. Everything she says is so lame and elementary. She's just not a very good teacher and her subjects are lame.
Nice when talking to her one on one. Kind of has a pretentions tone in her lectures. She assigns a lot of essays, but the class isnt too bad if you keep up with the reading.

What is this kindergarten? Perhaps I'm in the wrong class, at the wrong time? Oh may be it is the teacher - hmm...yes teacher. I don't know, may be it is just me, but I think it is very wrong to read Sherlock Holmes in college - don't you?
